Interface FlowHandle<A>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FlowHandleWithClientId<A>, FlowProgressHandle<A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FlowHandleImpl, FlowHandleWithClientIdImpl, FlowProgressHandleImpl

    @DoNotImplement
public FlowHandle<A>

    interface FlowHandle is a serialisable handle for the started flow, parameterised by the type of the flow's return value.
